    public class ScannerConfig.DecoderParams.Code39

    The Code39 class provides access to parameters that are available for the Code39 decoder.

      • length1

        public int length1
        Use to set decode lengths. The valid range is 0 to 55. 

         Example Usage:

      • length2

        public int length2
        Use to set decode lengths. The valid range is 0 to 55. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.length2 = 55;

      • verifyCheckDigit

        public boolean verifyCheckDigit
        Enable this feature to check the integrity of all Code 39 symbols to verify that the data complies with a specified check digit algorithm. The digital scanner decodes only those Code 39 symbols that include a modulo 43 check digit. Enable this feature only if the Code 39 symbols contain a modulo 43 check digit. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.verifyCheckDigit = false;

      • reportCheckDigit

        public boolean reportCheckDigit
        Transmit Code 39 data with or without the check digit. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.reportCheckDigit = true;

      • fullAscii

        public boolean fullAscii
        Code 39 Full ASCII is a variant of Code 39 that pairs characters to encode the full ASCII character set. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.fullAscii = true;

      • redundancy

        public boolean redundancy
        Sets the reader to read the barcode twice before accepting data. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.redundancy = true;

      • convertToCode32

        public boolean convertToCode32
        Code 32 is a variant of Code 39 used by the Italian pharmaceutical industry. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.convertToCode32 = true;

      • reportCode32Prefix

        public boolean reportCode32Prefix
        Scan the appropriate barcode to enable or disable adding the prefix character "A" to all Code 32 barcodes. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.reportCode32Prefix = true;

      • securityLevel

        public ScannerConfig.SecurityLevel securityLevel
        Options: Security level 0 , Security Level 1 , Security Level 2 and Security Level 3. Use enum ScannerConfig.SecurityLevel. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.securityLevel = SecurityLevel.LEVEL_1;

      • reducedQuietZone

        public boolean reducedQuietZone
        Flag to Enable or Disable decoding of Code 39 barcodes with reduced quiet zones. If you enable, select a OneDQuietZoneLevel to set the effort level. 

         Example Usage:
 	code39.reducedQuietZone = true;
